9bb"/><text x="688" y="58" fill="#00d4ff" font-size="10" text-anchor="middle" font-family="monospace">VOUT+</text><text x="688" y="296" fill="#00d4ff" font-size="10" text-anchor="middle" font-family="monospace">VOUT-</text><line x1="700" y1="70" x2="700" y2="76" stroke="#8899bb" stroke-width="1.4"/><line x1="700" y1="310" x2="700" y2="304" stroke="#8899bb" stroke-width="1.4"/><line x1="477" y1="170" x2="477" y2="310" stroke="#8899bb" stroke-width="1.4"/><circle cx="477" cy="310" r="2.6" fill="#8899bb"/><line x1="620" y1="70" x2="620" y2="340" stroke="#8899bb" stroke-width="1.4"/><rect x="585" y="340" width="70" height="34" fill="none" stroke="#8899bb" stroke-width="1.4"/><text x="620" y="361" fill="#c8d4ee" font-size="11" text-anchor="middle" font-family="monospace">TL431</text><line x1="585" y1="352" x2="510" y2="352" stroke="#8899bb" stroke-width="1.4"/><rect x="450" y="334" width="60" height="40" fill="none" stroke="#8899bb" stroke-width="1.4"/><text x="480" y="358" fill="#c8d4ee" font-size="11" text-anchor="middle" font-family="monospace">U2</text><text x="480" y="384" fill="#c8d4ee" font-size="8" text-anchor="middle" font-family="monospace">OPTO</text><line x1="450" y1="352" x2="210" y2="352" stroke="#8899bb" stroke-width="1.4"/><line x1="210" y1="352" x2="210" y2="249" stroke="#8899bb" stroke-width="1.4"/><line x1="210" y1="249" x2="240" y2="249" stroke="#8899bb" stroke-width="1.4"/><line x1="430" y1="310" x2="430" y2="352" stroke="#8899bb" stroke-width="1.4"/><line x1="430" y1="352" x2="424" y2="352" stroke="#8899bb" stroke-width="1.4"/><line x1="424" y1="344" x2="424" y2="360" stroke="#8899bb" stroke-width="1.4"/><line x1="416" y1="344" x2="416" y2="360" stroke="#8899bb" stroke-width="1.4"/><line x1="416" y1="352" x2="380" y2="352" stroke="#8899bb" stroke-width="1.4"/><line x1="380" y1="352" x2="380" y2="310" stroke="#8899bb" stroke-width="1.4"/><circle cx="380" cy="310" r="2.6" fill="#8899bb"/><text x="420" y="336" fill="#00d4ff" font-size="9" text-anchor="middle" font-family="monospace">CY</text><line x1="477" y1="20" x2="477" y2="60" stroke="#00d4ff" stroke-width="1" stroke-dasharray="4 3"/><line x1="477" y1="300" x2="477" y2="326" stroke="#00d4ff" stroke-width="1" stroke-dasharray="4 3"/><text x="477" y="14" fill="#00d4ff" font-size="8" text-anchor="middle" font-family="monospace">ISOLATION</text><path d="M280,70 H432 V310 H280 Z" fill="none" stroke="#eab308" stroke-width="8" stroke-opacity="0.4" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/><path d="M88,55 H170 M88,87 H170" fill="none" stroke="#ef4444" stroke-width="8" stroke-opacity="0.4" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/><path d="M230,70 H432 V236" fill="none" stroke="#ef4444" stroke-width="8" stroke-opacity="0.4" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg></div><div style="font-size:12px;margin:4px 0"><span style="display:inline-block;width:10px;height:10px;background:#eab308;margin:0 4px 0 10px"></span>Yellow = main loop (high current)<span style="display:inline-block;width:10px;height:10px;background:#ef4444;margin:0 4px 0 10px"></span>Red = high-voltage segments</div><strong>Main loop (yellow):</strong> bulk cap C1 → transformer primary → Q1 → sense resistor Rs → back to C1. The switching current flows around this loop while Q1 is on; it has the highest di/dt, so its layout area must be minimal and C1 must sit right next to the transformer and Q1.<br><strong>High-voltage segments (red):</strong> the AC lines after the fuse, the bridge, the HV+ DC bus (about 120-370VDC from 90-264VAC), and the primary winding down to the Q1 drain - at turn-off the drain also sees the reflected voltage plus the leakage spike, up to the 600V class.<br><strong>Why they overlap:</strong> the main loop runs on the HV bus itself - the C1 → primary → drain stretch is both the high-current path and a high-voltage node, so layout must serve EMI (smallest loop) and safety (creepage/clearance) at the same time.<div class="key-point">The interviewer is testing whether you can walk the current loop: find the bulk cap (the loop source), follow it around the switch = main loop; from the bridge output along the bus to the switch node = HV segments.</div>$vsq$, $vsq$8. Power-Circuit Loop Identification (Flyback)$vsq$, $vsq$八、電源回路のループ識別（フライバック）$vsq$, $vsq$8. 전원 회로 루프 식별(플라이백)$vsq$, $vsq$図はフライバック充電器の回路です。(1) 一次側の<strong>主ループ</strong>（スイッチングの大電流経路）、(2) 一次側の<strong>高電圧区間</strong>（ヒント：主ループと一部重なります）を示してください。展開して回路図と解答を確認。$vsq$, $vsq$<div class="exam-diagram-box"><svg viewBox="0 0 720 400" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"><rect width="720" height="400" fill="#0a0a1a"/><text x="16" y="59" fill="#00d4ff" font-size="11" text-anchor="middle" font-family="monospace">L</text><text x="16" y="91" fill="#00d4ff" font-size="11" text-anchor="middle" font-family="monospace">N</text><line x1="24" y1="55" x2="46" y2="55" stroke="#8899bb" stroke-width="1.4"/><rect x="46" y="49" width="34" height="12" fill="none" stroke="#8899bb" stroke-width="1.4"/><text x="63" y="45" fill="#c8d4ee" font-size="11" text-anchor="middle" font-family="monospace">F1</text><line x1="80" y1="55" x2="100" y2="55" stroke="#8899bb" stroke-width="1.4"/><line x1="24" y1="87" x2="100" y2="87" stroke="#8899bb" stroke-width="1.4"/><rect x="100" y="42" width="50" height="56" fill="none" stroke="#8899bb" stroke-width="1.4"/><text x="125" y="74" fill="#c8d4ee" font-size="11" text-anchor="middle" font-family="monospace">L1</text><text x="125" y="92" fill="#c8d4ee" font-size="8" text-anchor="middle" font-family="monospace">CM</text><line x1="150" y1="55" x2="170" y2="55" stroke="#8899bb" stroke-width="1.4"/><line x1="150" y1="87" x2="170" y2="87" stroke="#8899bb" stroke-width="1.4"/><rect x="170" y="42" width="60" height="56" fill="none" stroke="#8899bb" stroke-width="1.4"/><text x="200" y="74" fill="#c8d4ee" font-size="11" text-anchor="middle" font-family="monospace">BD1</text><line x1="230" y1="70" x2="420" y2="70" stroke="#8899bb" stroke-width="1.4"/><circle cx="280" cy="70" r="2