t="34" fill="none" stroke="#8899bb" stroke-width="1.4"/><text x="620" y="361" fill="#c8d4ee" font-size="11" text-anchor="middle" font-family="monospace">TL431</text><line x1="585" y1="352" x2="510" y2="352" stroke="#8899bb" stroke-width="1.4"/><rect x="450" y="334" width="60" height="40" fill="none" stroke="#8899bb" stroke-width="1.4"/><text x="480" y="358" fill="#c8d4ee" font-size="11" text-anchor="middle" font-family="monospace">U2</text><text x="480" y="384" fill="#c8d4ee" font-size="8" text-anchor="middle" font-family="monospace">OPTO</text><line x1="450" y1="352" x2="210" y2="352" stroke="#8899bb" stroke-width="1.4"/><line x1="210" y1="352" x2="210" y2="249" stroke="#8899bb" stroke-width="1.4"/><line x1="210" y1="249" x2="240" y2="249" stroke="#8899bb" stroke-width="1.4"/><line x1="430" y1="310" x2="430" y2="352" stroke="#8899bb" stroke-width="1.4"/><line x1="430" y1="352" x2="424" y2="352" stroke="#8899bb" stroke-width="1.4"/><line x1="424" y1="344" x2="424" y2="360" stroke="#8899bb" stroke-width="1.4"/><line x1="416" y1="344" x2="416" y2="360" stroke="#8899bb" stroke-width="1.4"/><line x1="416" y1="352" x2="380" y2="352" stroke="#8899bb" stroke-width="1.4"/><line x1="380" y1="352" x2="380" y2="310" stroke="#8899bb" stroke-width="1.4"/><circle cx="380" cy="310" r="2.6" fill="#8899bb"/><text x="420" y="336" fill="#00d4ff" font-size="9" text-anchor="middle" font-family="monospace">CY</text><line x1="477" y1="20" x2="477" y2="60" stroke="#00d4ff" stroke-width="1" stroke-dasharray="4 3"/><line x1="477" y1="300" x2="477" y2="326" stroke="#00d4ff" stroke-width="1" stroke-dasharray="4 3"/><text x="477" y="14" fill="#00d4ff" font-size="8" text-anchor="middle" font-family="monospace">ISOLATION</text><path d="M477,70 H600 V310 H477 V90" fill="none" stroke="#eab308" stroke-width="8" stroke-opacity="0.4" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg></div><div style="font-size:12px;margin:4px 0"><span style="display:inline-block;width:10px;height:10px;background:#eab308;margin:0 4px 0 10px"></span>Yellow = main loop (high current)</div><strong>Secondary main loop (yellow):</strong> secondary winding → output rectifier D3 → output capacitor Cout → back to the winding.<br><strong>Why minimum area:</strong> flyback secondary current is a <strong>pulsed high current</strong> that conducts only while Q1 is off, with very high di/dt; a larger loop means more parasitic inductance → worse ringing at D3 turn-off, voltage overshoot and radiated EMI. Cout ESL is part of the loop too, so put Cout tight against D3 and the winding pins, adding parallel MLCCs close-in when needed.<div class="key-point">The three flyback layout loops: primary hot loop (C1-P-Q1-Rs), secondary rectification loop (S-D3-Cout), and the gate-drive loop - naming all three wins half the interview.</div>$vsq$, $vsq$8. Power-Circuit Loop Identification (Flyback)$vsq$, $vsq$八、電源回路のループ識別（フライバック）$vsq$, $vsq$8. 전원 회로 루프 식별(플라이백)$vsq$, $vsq$同じフライバック回路で<strong>二次側主ループ</strong>（出力整流の大電流経路）を示し、このループ面積を最小にすべき理由を説明してください。$vsq$, $vsq$<div class="exam-diagram-box"><svg viewBox="0 0 720 400" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"><rect width="720" height="400" fill="#0a0a1a"/><text x="16" y="59" fill="#00d4ff" font-size="11" text-anchor="middle" font-family="monospace">L</text><text x="16" y="91" fill="#00d4ff" font-size="11" text-anchor="middle" font-family="monospace">N</text><line x1="24" y1="55" x2="46" y2="55" stroke="#8899bb" stroke-width="1.4"/><rect x="46" y="49" width="34" height="12" fill="none" stroke="#8899bb" stroke-width="1.4"/><text x="63" y="45" fill="#c8d4ee" font-size="11" text-anchor="middle" font-family="monospace">F1</text><line x1="80" y1="55" x2="100" y2="55" stroke="#8899bb" stroke-width="1.4"/><line x1="24" y1="87" x2="100" y2="87" stroke="#8899bb" stroke-width="1.4"/><rect x="100" y="42" width="50" height="56" fill="none" stroke="#8899bb" stroke-width="1.4"/><text x="125" y="74" fill="#c8d4ee" font-size="11" text-anchor="middle" font-family="monospace">L1</t