nline-block;width:10px;height:10px;background:#22c55e;margin:0 4px 0 10px"></span>Green = signal/noise path</div><strong>Feedback path (green):</strong> VOUT → divider resistors → TL431 (error amp vs. reference) → optocoupler LED → (across the isolation barrier) → optocoupler transistor → controller FB pin.<br><strong>What to stay away from:</strong> feedback is a high-impedance small signal - it fears coupling from the SW-node dv/dt and the main-loop di/dt most. Route away from the transformer, the Q1 drain and the RCD clamp; the divider midpoint (TL431 REF) is the most sensitive node, so put the divider next to the TL431 with the shortest traces; the two sides of the optocoupler belong to primary and secondary grounds respectively - never wander across regions for convenience.<div class="key-point">When the output oscillates or jitters for no reason, first check whether the FB trace runs alongside the SW node - the most common flyback layout failure.</div>$vsq$, $vsq$8. Power-Circuit Loop Identification (Flyback)$vsq$, $vsq$八、電源回路のループ識別（フライバック）$vsq$, $vsq$8. 전원 회로 루프 식별(플라이백)$vsq$, $vsq$出力電圧から制御 IC の FB ピンまでの<strong>フィードバック信号経路</strong>（TL431 とフォトカプラ経由）を示し、フィードバック配線がレイアウト上避けるべきものを説明してください。$vsq$, $vsq$<div class="exam-diagram-box"><svg viewBox="0 0 720 400" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"><rect width="720" height="400" fill="#0a0a1a"/><text x="16" y="59" fill="#00d4ff" font-size="11" text-anchor="middle" font-family="monospace">L</text><text x="16" y="91" fill="#00d4ff" font-size="11" text-anchor="middle" font-family="monospace">N</text><line x1="24" y1="55" x2="46" y2="55" stroke="#8899bb" stroke-width="1.4"/><rect x="46" y="49" width="34" height="12" fill="none" stroke="#8899bb" stroke-width="1.4"/><text x="63" y="45" fill="#c8d4ee" font-size="11" text-anchor="middle" font-family="monospace">F1</text><line x1="80" y1="55" x2="100" y2="55" stroke="#8899bb" stroke-width="1.4"/><line x1="24" y1="87" x2="100" y2="87" stroke="#8899bb" stroke-width="1.4"/><rect x="1